Grangeville first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Grangeville had a population of 508. The population density was {{convert|793.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Grangeville was 318 (62.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 7 (1.4%) [[African Americans|African American]], 6 (1.2%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 27 (5.3%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 80 (15.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 69 (13.6%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 171 persons (33.7%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Grangeville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0630686 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 171 households, out of which 67 (39.2%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 112 (65.5%) were married-couple households, 8 (4.7%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 20 (11.7%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 31 (18.1%) had a male householder with no partner present. 26 households (15.2%) were one person, and 7 (4.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.97.<ref name=DP1/> There were 139 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (81.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Grangeville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0630686 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 133 people (26.2%) under the age of 18, 63 people (12.4%) aged 18 to 24, 78 people (15.4%) aged 25 to 44, 148 people (29.1%) aged 45 to 64, and 86 people (16.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 40.2{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 91.7 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 178 housing units at an average density of {{convert|278.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 171 (96.1%) were occupied. Of these, 119 (69.6%) were owner-occupied, and 52 (30.4%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

